prompt.content:
Figure out the pattern in the below examples, and then answer with just "foo" or "bar".
(m, [e, t, y, v, m, b, w, k, h, u, p, o, z]) -> foo
(l, [a, k, j, x, i, p, d, h, e, w, o, m, n]) -> bar
(k, [i, x, n, t, u, c, g, o, w, y, p, m, z]) -> bar
(l, [b, q, f, c, j, y, m, e, u, a, x, d, n]) -> bar
(g, [b, h, z, o, x, l, g, i, u, w, m, k, v]) -> foo
(v, [a, h, l, p, t, o, f, w, r, x, q, c, n]) -> bar
(i, [x, w, c, j, a, m, b, f, g, h, q, k, d]) -> bar
(i, [u, n, q, a, v, w, p, e, f, z, h, s, j]) -> bar
(g, [s, w, k, g, u, p, m, o, e, i, r, d, l]) ->
